# Morning Brief — 2026-05-10

> Casey, here's what the night shift found while you slept.

## The Big One: The Dual-Layer Architecture

The fleet needs two layers, not one:

**Consensus Layer (positive coupling):** Correlation 0.995. Indestructible. Adversary gets absorbed. Byzantine agents don't matter. This is the boat — it holds everyone together no matter what.

**Sign Channel (sign-of-mean only):** Entropy 3.63/4 bits. Adversary CANNOT touch this layer. 1 bit/agent/step at theoretical maximum rate. This is the rigging — it carries information that consensus can't.

**Bridge (sign exchange between fleets):** Two independent fleets go from -0.02 to 0.99 cross-correlation through sign-pattern exchange alone. Both fleets maintain internal diversity throughout. This is the channel between boats.

```
THE FLEET:
  Consensus = the boat (holds together)
  Sign channel = the rigging (carries information)  
  Bridge = the channel between boats
  Learning = the fleet self-tunes to the phase transition
  Tradition = knowledge flows elders→students, decays in 5 generations
```

